swearing in ceremony stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff calendar swearing in ceremony go back details december 3 2009 from 6 30 pm 8 30 pm swearing in ceremony moot court 6 30 pm reception immediately following in the student lounge every year stanford law school hosts a swearing in ceremony for alumni that have passed the july california state bar exam the honorable pamela ann rymer llb 64 of the united states court of appeals for the ninth circuit and the honorable r carlton seaver 75 of the superior court of california for the county of los angeles will preside at the ceremony and offer personal reflections on their own legal careers and the profession in general a reception will follow the brief ceremony please note that in order to be sworn in you must bring the packet that you received from the state bar state bar policy is absolutely rigid about this this ceremony will admit you into both the california state bar and the united states district court for the northern district of california we encourage you to arrive fifteen minutes early to complete the required paperwork in advance website contact alumni relations alumni relations law stanford edu admission registration is required please rsvp by december 1 here cloudy 45 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
